Feature: Relashio

    A charm used to force someone or something to release that which it holds
    or grapples by means of shooting fiery sparks out or, underwater, shooting
    hot bursts of water.

    Pronunciation:
        /rɛˈlæʃi.oʊ/ re-LASH-ee-oh
    Seen/mentioned:
        Used by Harry against Grindylows in the second task of the Triwizard
        Tournament. When used more expertly by Bob Ogden in Half-Blood Prince,
        it threw Marvolo Gaunt backwards after an attempted attack. Hermione
        uses it in Deathly Hallows to free Mrs Cattermole from the chained
        chair.
